<br>
Roleplayers have NEEDS that are not being met by mainstream servers. Mainly that need is for an atmosphere that supports the &quot;willing suspension of disbelief.&quot; The ability to immerse yourself into your character.<br>
<br>
There are two parts to being able to maintain Suspension. First, is you need to have a support mechanism that encourages Suspension of disbelief. This is where the hardcore roleplaying comes in. This is where the fully roleplayed stuff comes in: &quot;Oh Brell, Please Turn Your Sacred Eye upon this poor gnome and bring his spirit back from the land of the dead into his body. By the Power Of Brell, I ressurect you!&quot; or the &quot;I must make my way across the long and dangerous plains of Karana, could you summon a wolf spirit into me so I might run with his speed?&quot; <br>
<br>
There are plenty of roleplayers here who are going to provide that support mechanism.<br>
<br>
The second part of maintaining Suspension is having an environment that is free of anti-RP totally OOC or d00dish comments. &quot;SOW PLZ&quot; &quot;NEED XP REZ!&quot; etc. <br>
<br>
Within these two extremes comes compatible non-RP and semi-RP behavior. &quot;Could someone give me a Wolf&quot; &quot;Could you resurrect my friend&quot; &quot;Can I get a heal please?&quot; Accepting this type of playstyle on a RP server is simply polite. To not do so makes one very irritating. I really don't care how non-RP someone is if they are willing to play along with the roleplaying environment and not interfere with anyone elses play style. <br>
<br>
But d00dspeak IS interfering with a playstyle. In the context of roleplayers, it is an offensive action. It is not non-roleplaying, it is ANTI-roleplaying. Putting up with it is NOT being polite, it is aiding and abetting an action that is harmful to the play needs of other players. Yes, we all have to get along, but part of getting along is respecting others. Part of respecting each other is respecting what this server is for: roleplaying.<br>
<br>
You can easily have a powergaming uberguild that is not RP and fits on this server. But it's got to fit into that &quot;compatible&quot; category. One guild that looks pretty uber to me seems to be doing this and nobody's chasing them with a stick--in fact they look kinda interesting. The other one is openly pushing for acceptance of anti-RP behavior and is gathering a pretty bad rep before server launch. <p>Numtini Lightheart <br>
Gnome Warrior<br>
Random Acts of Morell-Thule<br>Clockwork Tinkers Union of Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulazydog66.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LazyDog66</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/01 1:04:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why RPers are frustrated with Powergamers.</span><hr size=1> Numtini,<br>
